---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import DocsSidebar from "../../components/DocsSidebar.astro";
---
<Layout title="Authentication · flipagent docs">
	<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
		<div class="docs-shell">
			<DocsSidebar />
			<article class="docs-content">
				<h1>Authentication</h1>
				<p class="lead">Bearer tokens. Hashed at rest. Shown once at creation.</p>

				<h2>Key format</h2>
				<p>API keys carry the tier name inline — <code>fa_&lt;tier&gt;_&lt;32-char base64url random&gt;</code>. Total length varies with the tier name (40–44 chars):</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`fa_free_dCwI7zX3FQ8AgN-mZRoVtHs6jLBeUKy0
fa_hobby_dCwI7zX3FQ8AgN-mZRoVtHs6jLBeUKy0
fa_standard_dCwI7zX3FQ8AgN-mZRoVtHs6jLBeUKy0
fa_growth_dCwI7zX3FQ8AgN-mZRoVtHs6jLBeUKy0`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>The plaintext is shown to you exactly once at creation. We persist only an SHA-256 digest. The first 12 characters and the last 4 are stored separately so dashboards can render <code>prefix···suffix</code> for at-a-glance recognition without exposing the secret middle.</p>

				<h2>Send the key</h2>
				<p>Either header works:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`Authorization: Bearer fa_free_xxx
X-API-Key: fa_free_xxx`}</code></pre></div>

				<h2>Inspect a key</h2>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`curl https://api.flipagent.dev/v1/keys/me \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer fa_free_xxx"`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Returns tier, name, owner email, the display prefix + suffix, key timestamps, and credit usage. <code>resetAt</code> is <code>null</code> on Free (lifetime grant) and the next-month UTC boundary on paid tiers. <code>effectiveTier</code> may be lower than <code>tier</code> when a paid subscription is past_due — see <a href="/docs/rate-limits/">rate limits</a>.</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`{
  "id": "9cb48add-...",
  "tier": "free",
  "prefix": "fa_free_a3b1",
  "suffix": "UKy0",
  "name": "default",
  "ownerEmail": "you@example.com",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-01T12:34:56.000Z",
  "lastUsedAt": "2026-05-04T09:21:33.000Z",
  "usage": {
    "creditsUsed": 17,
    "creditsLimit": 500,
    "creditsRemaining": 483,
    "bonusCredits": 0,
    "resetAt": null,
    "effectiveTier": "free"
  }
}`}</code></pre></div>

				<h2>Revoke</h2>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`curl -X POST https://api.flipagent.dev/v1/keys/revoke \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer fa_free_xxx"`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Revoked keys return <code>401 invalid_key</code> on subsequent calls. Issue a new one from your <a href="/dashboard/">dashboard</a>.</p>

				<h2>Rate-limit headers</h2>
				<p>Every authenticated response carries credit-budget headers:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`X-RateLimit-Limit:           500
X-RateLimit-Remaining:       483
X-RateLimit-Reset:           2026-06-01T00:00:00.000Z   # paid tiers only
X-Flipagent-Credits-Charged: 1                          # what this call cost`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Hit zero and the next call returns <code>429 credits_exceeded</code> with <code>creditsUsed</code>, <code>creditsLimit</code>, and <code>resetAt</code> in the body. See <a href="/docs/rate-limits/">rate limits</a> for tier budgets and burst caps.</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
